node.text: Guys. Can we start a hiring chain by starting a sharing chain? I will do a live zoom call with two people who share this hiring chain post by @theofficialsting in their feed. Maybe you could offer to do a zoom call with one or two of your friends if they share in their feed as well. We’re all so starved for company in this pandemic. Someone in your feed would love to hang with you, i bet.  Let’s see how far we can get this post to go!! ❤️💛💙 @goodnews_movement @somegoodnews @coordown @tanksgoodnews

node.text: Let’s connect a little bit. -To be clear, because it seems it got muddy, I’ve always voted blue. I’m a Bernie girl and Biden/Harris has my vote. But I also know that polarization and externalizing human problems onto the “other side” doesn’t actually get us closer to fulfilling solutions. It’s time to listen to each other and try to understand and reflect so we can have real dialogue and walk into a brighter future together. And it’s time to start walking. The house is on fire. Let’s go, people. 🔥❤️

node.text: Going so slow. Savoring every breath and sip of my life today. Sending you love wherever you are. ❤️ @cpuigpottery

node.text: Two of my babies are in school. And I feel like I stumbled through a wardrobe time tunnel. #babies #littleladies #proudmama #maidenmother ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Caterina Scorsone on September 07, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and child.

node.text: This little babe started school today. With masks. And lots of protocols. -In the grand scheme of things, we figure it’s good that she’s there learning, playing, safe from zombies.

node.text: Hello, lovies! Last year I was honored to be awarded the GLOBAL Quincy Jones Advocacy Award. This year a beautiful feature on our family has been written for GLOBAL Down syndrome World Magazine. The work and research Global does directly impacts my daughter, Pippa, and families like mine. You can help support people with Down syndrome everywhere by making a donation to @globaldownsyndrome or signing up for their magazine. Link to the story in my Bio. #downsyndromeworld #downsyndromeworldmag #downsyndromeawareness #t21 #disibilityawareness #accessibility #diversityandinclusion #love 💛💙 @rebeccacoursey_photosandfilm

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Caterina Scorsone on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text: Haven’t posted in a minute. Here’s a quiet selfie in the kitchen. Luna’s been fed and is purring on the couch. Kitchen is clean. Everything is done. Everyone is safe and taken care of. I’m still on hiatus. And after I post this I am going to read a book made of paper and ink. I have a cup of tulsi tea and a candle that smells like a campfire. I can hear an owl outside. This is exquisite pleasure.
